article.description: Jacob Van scored 23 points and dished seven assists and Air Force beat San Jose State 83-61 on Saturday in a regular season finale.
article.headline: Van with 23 points leads Air Force over San Jose St. 83-61
article.linkText: Van with 23 points leads Air Force over San Jose St. 83-61
article.story: COLORADO SPRINGS, Colo. -- Jacob Van scored 23 points and dished seven assists and Air Force beat San Jose State 83-61 on Saturday in a regular season finale. Van was 6 of 10 from beyond the arc for the Falcons (12-18, 6-12 Mountain West Conference). Sid Tomes added 11 points and Trevor Lyons led the team with a career-best 13 rebounds in addition to his nine points. Van sank four 3-pointers in a first half that saw Air Force score 30 points from long range and the Falcons led all the way, building to a 50-28 advantage at halftime. Ryan Manning made back-to-back 3-pointers early in the second half to extend the Falcons lead to 64-41 with 11:44 to go and they cruised from there. Keith Fisher III led the Spartans (4-25, 1-17) with 18 points and eight rebounds.
